.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE CAKE-DIRT D "16 Mar 88" 1988
.RZ "DIRT CAKE" "A no-bake chocolate cake that looks like dirt"
Make and serve this cake in a clean plastic flower pot. You can enhance the
effect by putting a couple of "gummi worms" into the top of the cake, and
perhaps adding a plastic flower.
.IH "Serves 8\-12"
.IG "4 Tbsp" "butter" "60 g"
.IG "\(12 lb" "cream cheese," "250 g"
softened
.IG "1 cup" "powdered sugar" "150 g"
.IG "3\(12 cups" "milk" "850 ml"
.IG "7 oz" "instant vanilla pudding mix" "200 g"
.IG "12 oz" "whipped cream" "50 g"
.IG "1\(14 lb" "Oreo cookies," "600 g"
crushed in blender
.PH
.SK 1
Cream together the butter, cream cheese, and powdered sugar.
.SK 2
Mix milk, pudding, and whipped cream. Fold in to the butter-sugar mixture,
to make the filling.
.SK 3
Cover the hole in the bottom of the flower pot with a piece of waterproof
plastic tape. Put 1/3 of the crushed cookies on the bottom.
.SK 4
Cover with half of the filling 
.SK 5
Cover with another third of the crushed cookies.
.SK 6
Cover with the rest of the filling, then the remaining cookies.
.SK 7
Refrigerate overnight.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
10 minutes preparation, overnight chilling.
.I Precision:
approximate measurement OK.
.WR
David A. Rasmussen
University of Wisconsin at Milwaukee, Milwaukee, Wisconsin, USA
dave@csd4.milw.wisc.edu


